parameters: \n<Roselitte>"Is this... a hole...? Why has this suddenly appeared...?"

\n<Lyric>"Hmm... I can feel a faint magical power. It's like a plug
was in the hole. Maybe it's the work of the one we just
defeated."

\n<Roselitte>"...Let's turn back and check the cave again... With the
water receded... there might be new areas we can progress
through..."

\n<Ameria>"Yeah... but let's rest a bit, shall we? Roselitte-san, your
injury is..."
Roselitte fell to her knees on the ground.
Lyric grabbed Roselitte by the collar.

\n<Ameria>"I'm fine. I'm really fine. It's natural to get angry when
someone suddenly tries to touch a wound. So... okay? Let
go."
\n<Ameria>"No, it's okay... It's all my fault anyway."

\n<Ameria>"But, let's rest just a little...? If you collapse here,
it's all for nothing..."

parameters.name: 町・村っぽい感じ（夜っぽい）

parameters: \n<Lyric>"--So? Why did you get injured like that?"

\n<Lyric>"I'm not saying you have to talk if you don't want to. But
without knowing anything, I can't even offer a bit of
sympathy."

\n<Lyric>"So there was a proper reason for pushing Ameria away? It
wasn't just an accidental outburst, right?"
\n<Ameria>"Lyric, stop it... Thank you for worrying."
\n<Roselitte>"...A while ago, a certain military exercise was conducted."

\n<Roselitte>"From leading operational maneuvers and skill training to
organizing supply and medical systems. It was a large-scale
exercise that I led."

\n<Roselitte>"It happened on the final day of the exercise. The command
camp where I was located was attacked by someone."

\n<Roselitte>"The attackers were just a few swordsmen. And all of them
were reported to have excellent swordsmanship..."
\n<Lyric>"Reported? But you were there too, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"...I never imagined that we would be attacked right in the
middle of the command camp."
\n<Roselitte>"I was quickly taken down in that surprise attack."

\n<Roselitte>"Their target was me. And with my fall, the soldiers were
thrown into disarray, resulting in many casualties."
\n<Roselitte>"...And not a single one of the attackers was captured."

\n<Ameria>"...But who could have done it? Even with a surprise attack,
to inflict injury on Roselitte-san..."

\n<Roselitte>"It all happened in an instant; I had no time to confirm
their faces or appearances."

\n<Roselitte>"However, it seems there was someone among the attackers
with particularly exceptional sword skills. This wound is
likely from that person."

\n<Roselitte>"...And this is speculation, but I believe someone within
the empire must have facilitated the attack."

\n<Roselitte>"It's impossible to attack me at the heart of the military
during an exercise and escape without capture unless there
was an insider."

\n<Lyric>"...So that's how you got that wound. It's serious if it
left such lasting effects, even though you didn't die."

\n<Roselitte>"It was indeed a severe injury. However, it seems that this
scar and the aftereffects 'could have been treated'."

\n<Roselitte>"...This happened because an inexperienced medic who was
participating in the exercise treated my injury."
As she said this, Roselitte gently touched her wound.

\n<Roselitte>"Later examinations revealed that if I had received more
prompt and accurate treatment, there wouldn't have been any
aftereffects."
\n<Roselitte>"...But as you can see, the result is terrible."

\n<Roselitte>"That medic couldn't heal me. Because of that, they were
tried by the empire's court and are now confined in a prison
on the mainland."
\n<Lyric>"...That's too harsh. That medic saved you, right?"

\n<Roselitte>"Indeed, that medic saved me. If I ordered it, it would be
easy to release them from prison... but because of them..."

\n<Roselitte>"...Perhaps it would have been better if I had died
instead."

\n<Roselitte>"The ones at fault are the attackers and myself for being
completely off guard. I'm well aware of that."
\n<Roselitte>"...But even so. I hate the medic who couldn't heal me."
\n<Roselitte>"...Yes, I know. This is just resentment."

\n<Roselitte>"And that's why. I want that medic to remain in prison. To
be 'protected' under the law."

\n<Roselitte>"That way, I won't have to remember the medic's face or
name."

\n<Roselitte>"...I don't know anything about that medic. I've ordered the
imperial judiciary not to disclose any information about
them... because--"
Roselitte looked straight into Ameria's eyes.

\n<Roselitte>"'If they weren't 'protected', I might kill them. I don't
want to know anything."

\n<Roselitte>"...If it had been you who treated my injuries at that time,
perhaps things wouldn't have turned out this way."
\n<Ameria>"No, don't worry about it. How are you feeling?"

\n<Ameria>"That's good. If it gets tough again, rest right away! You
can't overdo it anymore, okay?"
\n<Ameria>"If it's too much, make sure to rest right away, okay?"

\n<Ameria>"Before we move on, let's make sure to check your injuries
properly, okay?"
\n<Roselitte>"No, for now I'm just a little... Please, later."
\n<Ameria>"I see... Understood. But don't push yourself too hard."
\n<Roselitte>"...I feel better after resting a little."
\n<Lyric>"You're not the one who should be saying that."
\n<Ameria>"Yeah, okay. You can move now, Roselitte-san."
\n<Roselitte>"...Understood. I feel a bit lighter now."
\n<Ameria>"Yeah, if that's the case, great! Hallelujah~♪"

Thanks to the treatment, the HP cost for skills has been
